{"questionId":"22224689","questionHtml":"<p>Show that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;for all values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>≥</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>R1</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>AG</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>discriminant&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>∆</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>∆</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;and concave up OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>∆</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;and coefficient of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;(may be seen in diagram)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>R1</em></strong></p>\n<p>hence&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>AG</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22224689","referenceCode":"24M.1.SL.TZ2.8ai","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that x2+2x+2>0 for all values of x.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.7—Solutions of quadratic equations and inequalities, discriminant and nature of roots"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}